  "local_port": 56736,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is GST? How is it different from CST and VAT?",
  "response": "**GST (Goods and Services Tax)** is a comprehensive, multi-stage, destination-based tax that is levied on every value addition in India. It replaced multiple indirect taxes like excise duty, VAT, and service tax, simplifying the tax structure. GST is collected at every stage of the supply chain, from manufacturing to the final sale, and is divided into three main components: CGST (Central GST), SGST (State GST), and IGST (Integrated GST for inter-state transactions).\n\n### **Key Differences Between GST, CST, and VAT:**\n\n| **Aspect**         | **GST**                          | **CST (Central Sales Tax)**      | **VAT (Value Added Tax)**        |\n|---------------------|----------------------------------|-----------------------------------|----------------------------------|\n| **Nature**          | A single, unified tax system.    | Tax on inter-state sales of goods.| Tax on intra-state sales of goods.|\n| **Applicability**   | Nationwide, both goods and services. | Only on inter-state sales of goods.| Only on intra-state sales of goods.|\n| **Tax Structure**   | Multi-stage, value-added tax.    | Single-stage tax (collected at sale).| Multi-stage, value-added tax.    |\n| **Input Tax Credit**| Allowed across the supply chain (CGST, SGST, IGST).| Not allowed (except for certain cases).| Allowed only within the state.    |\n| **Tax Rates**       | Uniform across India.            | Varies by state.                  | Varies by state.                 |\n| **Administration**  | Dual control by Central and State Governments.| Central Government.              | State Government.                |\n| **Compliance**      | Simplified, with a single return filing system.| Separate compliance for CST.     | Separate compliance for VAT.     |\n\n### **Summary:**\n- **GST** is a unified tax system that replaced multiple indirect taxes, including CST and VAT.\n- **CST** was a tax on inter-state sales and lacked input tax credit flexibility.\n- **VAT** was a state-level tax on intra-state sales, with limited input tax credit compared to GST.\n\nGST has streamlined the tax system, reduced tax cascading, and improved compliance efficiency.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
